# Project Orientation

Before writing or editing any code in this project, read `aiDocs/context.md`.

It contains:
- What the product is and what is explicitly out of scope
- The full tech stack and why each library was chosen
- Key conventions (SSE event schema, crisis gate behavior, tool naming, `.env` rules)
- A document map telling you which file to consult for deeper detail on any topic

## Quick Reference

| Need to know... | Read... |
|-----------------|---------|
| What to build and why | `aiDocs/prd.md` |
| Folder structure, Definition of Done | `aiDocs/mvp.md` |
| Component design, data flow, graph topology | `aiDocs/architecture.md` |
| Test tiers, pytest config, phase gates | `aiDocs/cliTestPlan.md` |
| Phase-by-phase build checklist | `ai/roadmaps/2026-03-16-mvp-roadmap.md` |
| Per-package implementation patterns | `ai/guides/` |
| All product changes made to date | `ai/changelog.md` |

## Non-Negotiables

- Never substitute a library from the tech stack without explicit instruction
- API keys live in `.env` only — never commit them
- The crisis gate is a hard pre-LLM keyword check — do not delegate it to the model
- After any code change, update `ai/changelog.md` (see `.cursor/rules/changelog.mdc`)
